node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Linnea on July 19, 2021. May be an anime-style image of 1 person.

node.text:
Sea witch🌊

I couldn’t decide on her hairstyle, so I’m posting both🙈 I like the straight hair because it’s got a crisp, graphic feel and ties the image together, but the wavy flowy hair looks pretty neat too and I spent way too much time on it for nobody to see it👿 tell me which one you prefer and help me decide, I’m chronically indecisive😭

Learning to draw digitally was a big mistake because every single pencil stroke is reversible and I spend hours just fiddling around with different color hues and shapes. With watercolor you just gotta embrace the mistakes and move on, but with digital you get to fixate in on every little flaw you see…

node.text:
A little pixie info sheet! in case you don’t know what they are and confuse them for fairies, god forbid😱 

At first I wanted to draw the pixie with nails holding down the wings and limbs (you know, like they do with butterflies and other bugs) buuut figured that might look a biiit to morbid…

if I have time I’ll make one for mermaids as well. If you got any other mythological creatures or cryptoids you’d think would look cool, lemme know!

node.text:
Another medical poster, this time giving a brief explanation on the mysterious way one might turn into a werewolf. I think I’ll make one more for vampirism, then I’m done!

I’ve never been super into werewolves, but I think I kind of am now. Is it too late for me to enter a wolf phase? They’re just so snarly and COOL

node.text:
Wanted to make a medical chart of the fictional Hanahaki disease! Maybe lycanthropy or symptoms of being haunted next? If you know of any cool supernatural ailments, let me know!

“The Hanahaki Disease is an illness born from one-sided love, where the patient throws up and coughs up flower petals when they suffer from one-sided love. The infection can be removed through surgery, but the feelings disappear along with the petals.”

What’s cooler than dinosaurs???? Dinos with rocks attached to them! Trust me, I’m a paleontologist.

I always feel awkward when I post my handwriting because it’s TERRIBLE. You might think it looks fine here, but its because I tried very, very hard. is it just me, or is it pretty common for artists to have bad handwriting? Please tell me its not just me🙈

Sketch on paper, colored digitally in Procreate

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Linnea on June 09, 2021 tagging @kuretakejapan. May be an illustration.

node.text:
@kuretakejapan sent me a set of their gorgeous new watercolor paints called Saiboku Shimbi Ink sticks, which I’ve tried out here! They’re definitely the prettiest set of paints I’ve ever owned, they’re so elegant😭

You use them by grinding up the pigment from the ink sticks on an ink stone, which you can then use as you would any watercolor. The colors are really vibrant, excited to play around with these some more! There’s something very soothing about grinding up your own paint, it’s almost meditative✨
